Leek my brother. I didn’t want to post this until we got back from vacation. Because I wanted to to truly celebrate you and what you’ve accomplished 

I’ve seen you have a lot of wins and I’ve seen you have a lot of losses. But one thing I still have yet to see, is you quit. No one I know has more perseverance than you . Most people see DJ leek and think that he has it all figured out, but I know the work and the determination that is behind what everyone sees today. You wrote your goals out and taped them to your wall. You packed up your DJ equipment in the rain,  you packed it on airplanes , you drove it across the country in a Uhaul. You did anything and everything to make your dreams happen and you’re gonna get rewarded for that. The world is going to know Malik Tuck. I could type for hours about all we been thru as brothers, but I know we have so much more to accomplish 

Tonight at The LEEK GALA. I’m going to support and celebrate you . 1 because you’ve always have celebrated me and 2 because you deserve it. I pray that everything you manifest and work towards comes to fruition . I’m glad that God knew we needed each other to change the world. Let’s go to the top my Leeko. Happy birthday to you. Love you forever my brother 🤞🏾 

SEE YALL AT THE LEEK GALLA TONIGHT. TICKETS ON SALE NOW ⭐️
